@startuml AI Interview Coach - System Flow

' Define participants
actor Candidate
participant "Frontend\n(React)" as Frontend
participant "WebSocket\nConnection" as WS
participant "Backend\nAPI" as Backend
participant "Session\nManager" as Session
participant "LLM Service\n(Gemini)" as LLM
participant "Video\nAnalyzer" as Video
participant "Audio\nAnalyzer" as Audio
participant "Feedback\nGenerator" as Feedback
database "PostgreSQL\nDatabase" as DB

' Authentication Flow
== Authentication & Setup ==
Candidate -> Frontend: Register/Login
Frontend -> Backend: POST /auth/register or /auth/login
Backend -> DB: Store/Verify user credentials
DB --> Backend: User data
Backend --> Frontend: JWT token
Frontend --> Candidate: Redirect to dashboard

' Session Creation Flow
== Session Creation ==
Candidate -> Frontend: Click "New Session"
Frontend -> Backend: POST /sessions/create\n(job_role, difficulty, duration)
Backend -> DB: Create session record
DB --> Backend: Session ID
Backend --> Frontend: Session details
Frontend --> Candidate: Show session configuration

' Interview Start Flow
== Interview Initiation ==
Candidate -> Frontend: Start Interview
Frontend -> Frontend: Request camera/mic permissions
Frontend --> Candidate: Show permission prompt
Candidate -> Frontend: Grant permissions
Frontend -> Frontend: Initialize MediaRecorder\n& SpeechRecognition
Frontend -> WS: Connect WebSocket\n(session_id)
WS -> Backend: WebSocket connection established
Backend -> Session: Initialize session manager
Session -> DB: Update session status = "active"
Backend -> WS: AUTH_SUCCESS message
WS -> Frontend: Connection confirmed

' Question Flow
== Question & Answer Flow ==
Backend -> LLM: Generate first question\n(based on job_role)
LLM --> Backend: Question object
Backend -> Session: Store question
Backend -> WS: NEXT_QUESTION message
WS -> Frontend: Display question
Frontend --> Candidate: Show question overlay\n(bottom-left corner)

Candidate -> Frontend: Start speaking answer
Frontend -> Frontend: Speech recognition\ncaptures transcript
Frontend -> WS: Send audio chunks\n(every 1 second)
WS -> Backend: Audio data + transcript
Backend -> Audio: Analyze audio\n(tone, pace, clarity)
Frontend -> WS: Send video frames\n(2 FPS)
WS -> Backend: Video frames
Backend -> Video: Analyze video\n(eye contact, gestures, expressions)

' Real-time Monitoring
== Real-time Analysis ==
loop Every few seconds
  Video -> Backend: Video analysis results\n(confidence, emotions)
  Audio -> Backend: Audio analysis results\n(speech rate, filler words)
  Backend -> Session: Check for issues\n(excessive fillers, poor eye contact)
  
  alt Issue Detected
    Session -> Backend: Generate intervention
    Backend -> WS: INTERVENTION message
    WS -> Frontend: Show intervention alert
    Frontend --> Candidate: Display warning/tip\n(e.g., "Maintain eye contact")
  end
end

' Answer Submission
== Answer Submission ==
alt User clicks "Done"
  Candidate -> Frontend: Click "Done" button
  Frontend -> Frontend: Stop speech recognition
  Frontend -> WS: SUBMIT_ANSWER\n(question, answer, duration)
else Auto-submit after silence
  Frontend -> Frontend: Detect 5s silence
  Frontend -> WS: SUBMIT_ANSWER\n(auto-triggered)
else User clicks "Skip"
  Candidate -> Frontend: Click "Skip" button
  Frontend -> WS: SUBMIT_ANSWER\n(empty answer)
end

WS -> Backend: Answer submission
Backend -> LLM: Evaluate answer quality
LLM --> Backend: Answer feedback\n(score, suggestions)
Backend -> Session: Store answer & feedback
Session -> DB: Save answer record
Backend -> WS: ANSWER_FEEDBACK
WS -> Frontend: Show feedback notification

' Next Question
Backend -> LLM: Generate next question
LLM --> Backend: Next question
Backend -> WS: NEXT_QUESTION
WS -> Frontend: Display next question
Frontend --> Candidate: Show new question

' Session Completion
== Session Completion ==
alt All questions answered
  Backend -> Session: Check question count
  Session -> Backend: All complete
else User ends early
  Candidate -> Frontend: Click "End Session"
  Frontend -> WS: END_SESSION
  WS -> Backend: End request
end

Backend -> Session: Finalize session
Session -> DB: Fetch all answers & analytics
DB --> Session: Session data
Session -> Feedback: Generate comprehensive feedback
Feedback -> LLM: Summarize performance
LLM --> Feedback: Overall assessment
Feedback --> Session: Final feedback report
Session -> DB: Update session status = "completed"
Backend -> WS: SESSION_COMPLETE\n(feedback, scores)
WS -> Frontend: Session complete data
Frontend --> Candidate: Show SessionComplete screen\n(scores, feedback, recommendations)

' Analytics View
== Post-Session Analytics ==
Candidate -> Frontend: View session results
Frontend -> Backend: GET /sessions/{id}/analytics
Backend -> DB: Fetch session analytics
DB --> Backend: Detailed metrics
Backend --> Frontend: Analytics data\n(charts, graphs, comparisons)
Frontend --> Candidate: Display interactive\nanalytics dashboard

@enduml
